data.name: CloseVaultWhenDirty_Message
data.value:
The operation you're about to perform will close current vault. However this vault has some unsaved changes. Please, resolve the conflict.
* "Save and Close" will save changes to the vault and then close it. * "Don't Save" will close the vault and discard all unsaved changes. * "Cancel" will cancel the operation and leave the vault open to perform manual fixup.

data.name: Version_UpgradeFailed
data.value: Upgrading vault from version '{0}' to version '{1}' (current) has failed. No data was lost, but you won't be able to work with the vault using the current version of the application.

data.name: Version_UpgradeSucceeded
data.value: Upgrading vault from version '{0}' to version '{1}' (current) has been successfully completed. Now you can proceed to working with the vault.

data.name: Version_UpgradeVaultToLatestVersion
data.value:
The vault you're opening has version '{0}' that doesn't match current version of the application ('{1}'). Do you wish to upgrade it?
If you decline the upgrade, the vault will not be opened and you won't be able to work with it using the current version of the application.
If you approve the upgrade, the vault will be converted to the new format, and its content will possibly undergo certain changes. However, before the upgrade the application will first make a backup of the vault, so not data will be lost.

data.name: ExitFailedDueToAnException_Message
data.value:
Your exit attempt has just failed due to an unexpected error. If this error persists the application wouldn't be able to shut down by itself.
The best bet would be to contact the developer for further instructions. Another option would be to forcibly close the application with a danger of DATA LOSS.
Do you wish to force application exit and accept risks of potential data loss (Yes) or return to application and try again (No)?
